menu "AkvaLink"

    config AKVALINK_BLE_ONLY
        bool "Build the standalone BLE-only variant (no Matter)"
        default n
        help
            Build the --ble AkvaLink variant: skip Matter/Thread/Wi-Fi and
            run a standalone NimBLE GATT server (Device Information, Environmental
            Sensing temperature, and a custom AkvaLink service with uptime).

            Use this for homes with no Matter hub and no Wi-Fi — a phone/app
            connects directly over BLE. Select via the launcher's --ble flag
            (which layers sdkconfig.defaults.ble on top of sdkconfig.defaults).

    config AKVALINK_SENSOR_TEST
        bool "Build the sensor-only test variant (no Matter, no BLE)"
        default n
        help
            Build the --sensor test variant: skip Matter and BLE entirely
            and just read the sensor (DS18B20) over 1-Wire, logging the
            temperature. Use it to verify probe wiring and the sensor before
            building the full app.

    config AKVALINK_AP
        bool "Build the Wi-Fi AP variant (SoftAP + web page, no Matter/BLE)"
        default n
        help
            Build the --ap AkvaLink variant: run an OPEN Wi-Fi SoftAP named
            "AkvaLink" hosting a captive web page that shows the live DS18B20
            temperature. No Matter, no BLE, no home network — any phone or
            laptop joins the AP and the page opens.

            NOTE: an always-on SoftAP keeps the Wi-Fi radio awake and is NOT
            battery friendly (days, not years) — for mains/USB-powered use.
            Select via the launcher's --ap flag.

    config AKVALINK_STATION
        bool "Build the Wi-Fi station variant (BLE-provisioned client, no Matter)"
        default n
        help
            Build the --station AkvaLink variant: join the home Wi-Fi as a
            client, provisioned over BLE with Espressif Unified Provisioning
            (the free "ESP BLE Provisioning" app). Once online it advertises
            mDNS "akvalink.local" and serves the temperature page. No Matter,
            no hub — the phone/app talks to it directly on the LAN.

            NOTE: staying associated keeps the Wi-Fi radio reachable — lighter
            than the SoftAP variant but still not multi-year on a coin cell.
            Select via the launcher's --station flag.

endmenu
